<div type="description" n="monument">
<head>Description of Monument</head>

<p>Two joining fragments of a <rs type="material" key="marmor">white marble</rs> <rs type="objectType">statue base</rs> with moulding above and below on all sides (<measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">0.67</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.32</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth">0.57</measure>) damaged at lower left corner, on top front moulding and back left corner. Fragments of the statue have been published (see bibliography).</p></div><div type="description" n="text"><head>Description of Text</head><p><rs type="execution" key="scalpro">Inscribed</rs> on the face.</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="letters">
<head>Letters</head>
<p>l.1, <measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre">0.028</measure>; l.2, <measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre">0.03</measure></p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="date">
<head>Date</head>
<p>
<date notBefore="0014" notAfter="0069" exact="both">Julio-Claudian</date>
(<rs type="criteria">context</rs>, <rs type="criteria">lettering</rs>)</p>
</div>
<div type="edition" lang="grc">
<head lang="en">Edition</head>
<ab><lb n="1"/>  <persName type="emperor" full="yes"><name type=" " reg="Δροῦσος">Δροῦσον</name>  <name reg="Καῖσαρ">Καίσαρα</name>  <lb n="2"/><persName type="emperor" full="yes"><name reg="Τιβέριος" type="praenomen">Τιβερίου</name></persName>  <w lemma="υἱός">υἱόν</w>  </persName></ab>
</div>


<div type="translation">
<head>Translation</head>
<p>(Statue of) Drusus Caesar, son of Tiberius.</p>
</div>
<div type="commentary">
<head>Commentary</head>
<p>One of the Sebasteion group of dedications to the imperial family (<xref type="inscription" n="1315" href="090037">9.37</xref>=72.224, <xref type="inscription" n="1316" href="090038">9.38</xref>=72.237, <xref type="inscription" n="1317" href="090039">9.39</xref>=72.275, <xref type="inscription" n="1318" href="090040">9.40</xref>=73.145, <xref type="inscription" n="1296" href="090033">9.33</xref>=77.123, <xref type="inscription" n="1288" href="090026">9.26</xref>=80.172, <xref type="inscription" n="1289" href="090027">9.27</xref>=82.108, <xref type="inscription" n="1298" href="090035">9.35</xref>=82.109, <xref type="inscription" n="1290" href="090028">9.28</xref>=82.116, <xref type="inscription" n="1297" href="090034">9.34</xref>=82.117, <xref type="inscription" n="1291" href="090029">9.29</xref>=82.118, <xref type="inscription" n="1299" href="090036">9.36</xref>=82.210, <xref type="inscription" n="1293" href="090030">9.30</xref>=84.30, <xref type="inscription" n="1294" href="090031">9.31</xref>=84.31, and  <xref type="inscription" n="1295" href="090032">9.32</xref>=84.41). On these see <bibl n="jmr1996b"><author>Reynolds</author> (1996), <title level="a">Ruler-cult at Aphrodisias</title></bibl>.</p><p>For another dedication to Drusus see <bibl><title level="m"> Jahreshefte</title> 53 (1981/82), 155, no.144</bibl>. There, however, father and son receive their full titulature. Tiberius' lack of titles might suggest a date before his accession, or after his death.</p>
</div>
